 ve Auditorium
GEO:39.170002;-86.517492
SUMMARY:Special Event: A Conversation about U.S.-Taiwan Relations with Al
 exander Yui (Taiwan's Representative to the U.S.)
DESCRIPTION:Representative Yui's talk\,&#160\;A Trustworthy Taiwan-U.S. P
 artnership\,&#160\;will begin at 2:00pm\, followed by a conversation with
  Provost Ciorciari and a Q&amp\;A session.&#160\;The event will conclude 
 with a musical performance featuring IU Jacobs School faculty and student
 s\, part of the IU-Taiwan Collaborations in Music Project\, followed by a
  reception for registered attendees in the Atrium.&#160\;  Alexander Tah-
 Ray Yui is Taiwan's Representative to the United States\, a role he assum
 ed in December 2023. He has over 35 years of experience in diplomacy and 
 most recently served as Taiwan's Representative to the European Union and
  Belgium and as Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs. Throughout his career\,
  he has worked to expand Taiwan's global partnerships and strengthen its 
 international presence. He has participated in executive education progra
 ms at UPenn\, LSE\, and Harvard.&#160\;  This special event is presented 
 by the Hamilton Lugar School\, the East Asian Studies Center\, the Taiwan
  Studies Initiative\, and the East Asia and the World speaker series.&#16
 0\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Representative Yui's talk\,&#160\;<stro
 ng>A Trustworthy Taiwan-U.S. Partnership\,&#160\;</strong>will begin at 2
 :00pm\, followed by a conversation with Provost Ciorciari and a Q&amp\;A 
 session.&#160\;The event will conclude with a musical performance featuri
 ng IU Jacobs School faculty and students\, part of the IU-Taiwan Collabor
 ations in Music Project\, followed by a reception for registered attendee
 s in the Atrium.&#160\;</p><p>  Alexander Tah-Ray Yui is Taiwan's Represe
 ntative to the United States\, a role he assumed in December 2023. He has
  over 35 years of experience in diplomacy and most recently served as Tai
 wan's Representative to the European Union and Belgium and as Vice Minist
 er of Foreign Affairs. Throughout his career\, he has worked to expand Ta
 iwan's global partnerships and strengthen its international presence. He 
 has participated in executive education programs at UPenn\, LSE\, and Har
 vard.&#160\;</p><p>  This special event is presented by the Hamilton Luga
 r School\, the East Asian Studies Center\, the Taiwan Studies Initiative\
 , and the East Asia and the World speaker series.&#160\;</p>
