DTSTART:20260411T230000Z
DTEND:20260412T003000Z
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
SUMMARY:AsianFest 2026 Mosaic Traditions: Piecing a Common Ground
DESCRIPTION:The Asian Culture Center In collaboration with the City of Bl
 oomington Community and Family Resources Department presents 2026 Asianfe
 st\, an annual campus-community partnership featuring cultural and inform
 ation tables\, performances\, and video clips/slides about Asian American
  and Pacific Islander heritage.  &#160\;Mosaic Traditions: Piecing a Comm
 on Ground highlights the enduring legacy of asian art forms evolving thro
 ugh generations.&#160\;  &#160\;  The tales we tell&#160\;and the stories
  we share all bear our past\, present\, and futureŌĆöacross time and spac
 e.&#160\; And thus\, we meet&#160\;together\, where cuisines merge in fus
 ion\, attire becomes fashion\, music&#160\;becomes memories\, and trends 
 become traditions.&#160\;  &#160\;  We all possess&#160\;both ancestral w
 isdom and foresight that converge&#160\;in the present\, reminding us to 
 learn from the past while remaining prudent in facing the future. &#160\;
   &#160\;  Welcome to AsianFest 2026\, where we celebrate our shared hist
 ories and unique heritages. Through this year's theme\, Mosaic Traditions
 : Piecing a Common Ground\, we invite one and all&#160\;to find peace on 
 common ground.&#160\;  &#160\;  This event is part of 2026 Asian American
  and Pacific Islander Heritage Month.  &#160\;All Indiana University even
 ts\, groups\, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and histori
 cal observances welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana 
 University community.For more information\, view this event in BeInvolved
  (https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12011874).
